Print It! - A visual LPR printer written in C# by Rick Dove
Usage: 1) Press the 'Select file' button and choose the PRN file you wish to print 2) Enter the IP address of the destination printer into the IP Address box 3) Press the Print It! button and your file will print
Note: When using the 'Enable LPR' button you will need to launch this program as an administrator To do this, right click the application before launching and select the 'Run as administrator' option
Enabling LPR is a one time operation on the machine on which this software is run. The enable LPR button simply installed the LPR Port Monitor Service using the DISM command which will allow your system to print PRN files via LPR
